			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">sk/mage guide. mainly for xp groups.
<br />

<br />
if any of this is usefull, feel free to rip the info and slice it however you feel fit.
<br />

<br />
and i apologize in advance for my crappy spelling=)
<br />

<br />

<br />
pets:
<br />

<br />
reguardless of weather or not the pet is a rogue, if possible, put the pet to the mobs back as it will help it do more damage, and stop it from taking reposts or eating rampages. as an sk, you should be used to doing this with your pet.
<br />

<br />
get all the pet goodies for your pet as an sk. the the 58 sk pet is a 44 necro pet. with a muzzle, a belt, and a pair of proccing blades, he's no joke. (and every little bit helps)
<br />

<br />
if the pet is a skinny pet (water, air, fire) don't let him take die if you can soak a few hits. all you have to do is get within melee range of the mob and the pet will continue to do his damage while you soak the hits. if a mob is slowed or your have a CH coming, the extra bit of damage can mean the difrence of the pets damage output versus the downtime of a mage haveing to resummon his pet.
<br />

<br />
if the pet is a big meaty pet (epic, earth) part of the pets shtick is that he's got hp. if you get one too many adds and the mage sends his earth pet out to keep one tied up abit away, let it. just watch the pets HP, 'cus when that pet dies, it may go for the mage. perhaps steping closeby and soaking a few hits while a pet heal lands or a new one is summoned can keep the mage up and running. also note it can be good to keep boney joe backed off the mob that the earthy is tanking, as he'll inevitably be a bone tinted stain on the pavement.
<br />

<br />
work with the pets you have. if it is a water pet, keep it behind. you've had plenty of practice with your own pet, this should be natural. if it's a rooting pet, get up close into the mobs face and tell other group members to fight at max melee distance. work with what you have as they are alwayse handy.
<br />

<br />
for the purpose of mob placement, it can be good to ask all pet casters in the group to turn taunt off. Somtimes when you need to pull a mob around to keep it centered, off of walls, keep it from falling off a bridge, etc, the pets taunting can keep the monster from following you properly, leading to pet, and possibley caster damage that is unneccisary. 
<br />

<br />
alwayse do mad sk agro, never any reason not to.
<br />

<br />
summoned stuff
<br />

<br />
sk's are a wacky hybrid, they can make use out of a whole slew of summoned stuff.
<br />

<br />
pet toys. alwayse get your pet toyed up. if you are pulling, and don't want a pet, that is understandable, but if you are the main tank, there is no reason not to use starvin marvin. he can /sheild you for a few hundred damage or more, he's free dps(kinda like a dot you don't pay for) and with pet proccing weapons and a muzzel, he's no laughing matter(unless he tries to tank)
<br />

<br />
a big chunk of dps for sk's can come from spears. with a kei and Mental corruption, an sk can cast 2 spears as soon as they pop, fairly continuously. as such, the mage summoned improved damage bracer helps this out nicely. its stats arn't the best, but if your looking to do damage, they hit home. also note the mana saving neck can help you save mana for spears. more mana over time = more damage over time.
<br />

<br />
as mentioned above, the mana saving neck is handy for...saving mana.
<br />

<br />
mod rod. let me say that again. mod rod. mod rods are the thing i love mages for more than anything. when they have good mana, and can keep tossing rods at you (especialy the 3 charge ones) your dps via spears and dots can rise dramaticly. and if you happen to be the main tank (which is the primary reason to xp with an sk) you have a complete heal coming at you fairly often, so if you time your rod use when the CH is going to land, its 'free' mana in the sense that it doesn't require somone to go back and clean your hp up. 450 damage may scare your cleric, but if he's cutting it that close that it matters, your cleric should loosen up and not try to save every iota of mana. in summery, mod rods rock.
<br />

<br />
sk's can shoot bows for beans. but they are handy for pulling if they hit or not. So ofcourse, summoned arrows can be handy.
<br />

<br />
if the mage asks you to move for a bolt, do it. you should have such tight controll over the mob that you can move it around the camp as necisary.
<br />

<br />
as an sk tank, my number 1 class to find as dps of an xp group is a mage. a good mage is a boon to an sk, i spent a long time leveling with one (and a bst, so i love'm both:p) so i've developed an apreciation of them.
<br />

<br />
-slagnath, revenant of drinal.
<br />

<br />

<br />
-ps if any of  that info is usefull, as i said, dice it up and word it however you want.
<br />

<br />
(edited for stupid typo's)<br />_________________<br /><img src=http://members.cox.net/working/slaggy.jpg>
<br />

<br />
wurd grobb
<br />
never forgive, never forget</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
