			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I didnt see it mentioned but thought I would mention:
<br />

<br />
Tanks:
<br />
When possible, move so that all pets (not just mages) are at the back of the mob.  This greatly increases group DPS.  Also, it IS your job to move so that all PCs and pets are at the back of the mob during Enrage.  The mob should be facing nobody but you at all times during normal exp groups.  
<br />

<br />
If you need to reposition, then ask for help.  Pet classes will move pets as needed.  In addition, a good mage will agro-move a mob to where they like (away from walls and into the middle of the room).  This is a learned ability and something mages are good at.  Dont get worried or frustrated if a mob sudenly moves from a wall to the middle of the room.  Its usually done for good reason.
<br />

<br />
CC:
<br />
Mage pets will easily CC slowed mobs.  Good mages will often agro-pull mobs away from the group and then set their pet on them.  If the mob is already controlled by the mage pet, leave it.  Not only its it under control, but it is also taking damage and speeding up the killing process.  At higher levels, mages can easily control agro and dictate the fight.  So let them CC mobs to speed up the killing and reduce cleric/enchanter mana consumption.  
<br />

<br />
In addition, it makes much more sense to have ole Jobober taking a beating rather than a bard that could be doing much more group beneficial activities.
<br />

<br />
Casters:
<br />
Use the damn mod rods.  At higher levels, with some gear and AAs, a mage can sustain a huge DPS and provide you with free mana.  Take advantage of it.  Do yourself a favor and have an open spot for a right clicky.  Stick the rod in there and use it often.  Good mages will often spam the group with "Who needs a rod?" more to *remind* you to use it rather than asking if you need a new one.  With the LDON speed groups needed, rods are a huge plus.
<br />

<br />
Shaman:
<br />
Malo for the mage.  In fast paced higher level groups, you maloing means the difference of 2k to 6kd per mob.  Do it.  Its worth it to everyone.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
